               <head>Two Persian texts on musicology, the second illustrated.</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary> Two texts on musicology bound together: <title>Shams al-Aṣvāt</title>
                     (Sun of Songs, albeit here entitled <title>Dar ‘Ilm-i Musīqī</title>, On
                     Musicology), and <title key="work_22270">Ḥayy al-Arvāḥ</title> (Life of the Souls) by amateur
                     musician Mīyān Zīyā al-Dīn, pen-named 'īyā', with various instruments drawn in
                     the margins. </summary>
               </msContents>
